     <body>
     <div type="dedication">
   <pb facs="110"/>
   <head>❧ To my worthy and honored <hi>friend, Sir Walter Aston</hi> Knight of the Bath.</head>
   <p>
      <hi>
         <seg rend="decorInit">S</seg>IR, though without suspition of flatterie I might in more ample and free tearmes, in<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>timate my affection vnto you, yet hauing so sensible a taste of your generous and noble aisposition, which without this habite of ceremony can estimate my loue: I will ra<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ther affect bre<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 span">
            <desc>〈…〉</desc>
         </gap>, though it should seeme my fault, than by my tedious complement, to trouble mine owne opinion set<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>led in your iudgement and discretion. I make you the Pa<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>tron of this Epistle of the</hi> Blacke-Prince, <hi>which I pray you accept, till more easie houres may offer vppe from mee some thing more worthy of your view, and my trauell.</hi>
   </p>
   <closer>
      <signed>Yours truely deuoted,
Mich: Drayton.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
